<s> Simple summary of a basic point: Sure, we're text-oriented in the comments we sent -- that's our specialization.  </s>
<s> However, no Web-based authoring protocol can afford to ignore textual data.  </s>
<s> I'm not sure that we make very many special requests that could _never_ be useful for non-textual data, but if we do that's not an argument against them.  </s>
<s> It is merely an argument that DAV shouldn't require the use of text-oriented facilities for non-textual data.  </s>
